# Metrics + Monitoring (audric side)

The audric web app is the producer for every metric the agent generates. The split:

| Goes to | Who reads it |
|---|---|
| Prisma (`TurnMetrics`, `SessionUsage`, `ConversationLog`, `AppEvent`, `AdviceLog`) | Q5/Q6 dashboards, harness regression analysis, billing |
| Vercel Observability | On-call alerting, perf regressions |
| Vercel Speed Insights | LCP/FCP/TTI for chat UI |
| CloudWatch | t2000 ECS task health (cron, indexer) |

## TurnMetrics — the harness telemetry table (Spec 1)

Every chat turn writes one row. Every confirmed/declined/modified pending action updates the row via `attemptId`-keyed `updateMany`. Resume turns get their own row.

Schema highlights (see `prisma-models-overview.mdc` for full list):

- `sessionId`, `turnIndex` — pair (legacy fallback for resume key)
- `attemptId` — UUID v4, primary resume key (Spec 1 Item 3)
- `pendingActionOutcome` — `confirmed | declined | modified | resume_failed | unresolved | null`
- `modifiableFieldsTouched` — JSON of which fields the user edited (Spec 1 Item 6)
- `writeToolDurationMs` — time from confirm → execute response
- `inputTokens`, `outputTokens`, `cacheReadTokens`, `cacheWriteTokens`, `costUsd`
- `engineVersion`, `model`, `complexityClass`, `thinkingEffort`
- `toolNames`, `toolDurationMs` (per-tool)

Where it's written:
- `apps/web/app/api/engine/chat/route.ts` — chat-time row
- `apps/web/app/api/engine/resume/route.ts` — outcome update + resume turn row
- `apps/web/lib/engine/harness-metrics.ts` — the helper functions

## SessionUsage — billing + cost tracking

One row per session. Drives the billing gate (5 unverified / 20 verified turns per rolling 24h). Written at session end by `lib/engine/log-session-usage.ts`.

## ConversationLog — full transcripts

Every role + content + toolCalls + tokens + cost. Used for the future self-hosted model migration training data.

> **Deleted in v0.7d Phase 6 Block A (S.221, 2026-05-21):** the memory-extraction cron (`UserMemory` writes) + profile-inference cron (`UserFinancialProfile` writes) that used to consume ConversationLog rows. Long-term memory is now extracted live in-turn by MemWal `analyze()` (see `apps/web-v2/lib/audric/memwal-write-callback.ts`).

## AppEvent — chip taps + sponsor failures + key flows

Used by the t2000 ECS indexer + various analytics surfaces.

> **Deleted in v0.7d Phase 6 Block A (S.221):** the 7 chain-memory classifiers that consumed AppEvent → `ChainFact`. MemWal now absorbs chain signal organically from chat; LLM reads fresh chain state on demand via tools.

## What MUST NOT happen

```typescript
// ❌ Skip TurnMetrics because "the turn was simple"
// — EVERY turn writes a row. Always.

// ❌ Forget attemptId on TurnMetrics
prisma.turnMetrics.create({ data: { sessionId, turnIndex /* no attemptId */ } });
// — resume route can't find the row → outcome telemetry lost

// ❌ Write to a vendor we haven't approved
fetch('https://api.axiom.co/...');
// — Vercel + CloudWatch + Prisma. Adding new vendors needs roadmap approval.

// ❌ Log PII in plaintext to console
console.log(`User email: ${email}, address: ${address}, amount: ${amount}`);
// — structured logging only. Use the helpers in lib/errors.ts.

// ❌ Synchronous metric write on the critical path
await prisma.turnMetrics.create(...);  // adds 50ms to every turn
return Response.json(...);
// — fire and forget with .catch() instead.
```

## Read paths

- Daily spend → `prisma.sessionUsage.aggregate({ _sum: { costUsd: true } })`
- Pending action outcome distribution → `prisma.turnMetrics.groupBy({ by: ['pendingActionOutcome'] })`
- Tool latency p95 → custom query against `toolDurationMs` JSON column
- Resume failure rate → `prisma.turnMetrics.count({ where: { pendingActionOutcome: 'resume_failed' } })`

## Adding a new metric

1. Decide: durable (Prisma) or transient (Vercel/CloudWatch)?
2. If durable, extend `TurnMetrics` (preferred) or add a model. Add `@@index` on filter columns.
3. Update `prisma-models-overview.mdc` if a new model.
4. Backfill if it's meaningful for past sessions (run a one-off migration).
5. Document the dashboard query.

## SLOs (Service Level Objectives) — published 2026-05-09 (SPEC 19 Phase D, S.135)

These are the v1.24.13 baselines + targets for the agent's hot path. The targets are anchored to current measured p95 with ~20% headroom (per D-4 in SPEC 19); any breach triggers an alert. Re-evaluate every quarter and tighten as the baseline improves.

### Latency SLOs

| Metric | p50 baseline | p95 baseline | p50 target | p95 target | Alert threshold |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| `audric.engine.resume_stream_duration_ms` (standalone write) | 1.4s | 2.2s | < 1.8s | < 2.7s | p95 > 3.0s for 5min |
| `audric.engine.resume_stream_duration_ms` (bundle, 2 ops) | 2.4s | 2.6s | < 2.7s | < 3.2s | p95 > 3.5s for 5min |
| `audric.engine.chat_stream_duration_ms` (first turn, cache write) | 2.2s | n/a | < 2.5s | < 3.0s | p95 > 3.5s for 5min |
| `audric.txn.prepare_duration_ms` | 350ms | 800ms | < 500ms | < 1.0s | p95 > 1.5s for 5min |
| `audric.txn.execute_duration_ms` | 700ms | 1.5s | < 900ms | < 2.0s | p95 > 2.5s for 5min |
| `engine.pwr.total_ms` (standalone, cache hit) | 30ms | 90ms | < 50ms | < 150ms | p95 > 300ms for 5min |
| `engine.pwr.total_ms` (bundle, 2-tool refresh) | 730ms | 1.1s | < 850ms | < 1.4s | p95 > 2.0s for 5min |
| `anthropic.latency_ms` (Haiku, low effort, no thinking) | 1.4s | 2.0s | < 1.8s | < 2.5s | p95 > 4.0s for 5min |

### Reliability SLOs

| Metric | Baseline | Target | Alert threshold |
|---|---|---|---|
| `external.retry_count{vendor:bv, outcome:retried_success}` rate | < 2% | < 5% | > 10% over 15min |
| `external.retry_count{vendor:bv, outcome:exhausted}` rate | < 0.05% | < 0.1% | > 0.5% over 15min |
| `external.retry_count{vendor:anthropic, outcome:retried_success}` rate | < 0.5% | < 2% | > 5% over 15min |
| `external.retry_count{vendor:anthropic, outcome:exhausted}` rate | ~0% | < 0.1% | > 0.3% over 15min |
| `external.retry_count{vendor:sui, outcome:retried_success}` rate | n/a (low traffic) | < 5% | > 15% over 15min |
| `external.retry_count{vendor:sui, outcome:exhausted}` rate | ~0% | < 0.1% | > 0.5% over 15min |
| `audric.harness.bundle_outcome_count{outcome:executed}` rate (of all bundles) | 100% (sample=5) | > 98% | < 95% over 1h |
| `audric.harness.post_write_refresh_outcome{outcome:ok}` rate | 100% (sample=11) | > 99% | < 97% over 1h |
| `bv.cb_open` gauge (BlockVision circuit breaker) | 0 | 0 (transient OK) | open > 3 times per hour |

### Cost SLOs (per the 5/20 daily-free billing gate)

| Metric | Target | Alert threshold |
|---|---|---|
| `SessionUsage.costUsd` per session p95 | < $0.10 | p95 > $0.20 over 24h |
| `SessionUsage.costUsd` daily total | < $50 (current scale) | day-on-day +50% |
| `audric.tokens` (cumulative input) per turn | < 25k tokens | p95 > 40k over 24h |

### Cache health SLOs

| Metric | Target | Alert threshold |
|---|---|---|
| `wallet.cache_hit{freshness:fresh}` rate | > 70% | < 50% over 1h |
| `defi.cache_hit{freshness:fresh}` rate | > 80% | < 60% over 1h |
| `defi.cache_hit{freshness:stale-served}` rate | < 5% (steady state) | > 15% over 15min (BV degradation signal) |

### How SLOs are observed

- **Vercel Observability dashboard** (read-only mode): filter by metric `name`, group by tag, chart 7-day p50/p95/p99.
- **Alerts** are wired via Vercel Observability monitor rules. Each alert is paged to the on-call channel; thresholds above match the table.
- **Quarterly tightening** (per D-4 in SPEC 19): re-snapshot baselines from production, narrow targets if p95 has dropped > 20%. Document the new baseline + the change date inline in this table.

